<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China To Lower Bank Interest Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China (PBOC)
announced today that it will further lower the interest rates of
local banks beginning Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to a PBOC announcement, the annual rates will be
decreased by an average 0.49 percentage points for deposits, 1.12
percentage points for loans, 1.71 percentage points for reserved
funds, and 1.82 percentage points for second loans.
</P>
<P>
The central bank reiterates that all financial institutions,
including savings deposit agencies run by the postal departments,
must strictly follow the state policy on bank rates.
</P>
<P>
 
</P>
</TEXT>
