<HEADLINE> 4 People Injured by Explosions in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Four people were injured Tuesday in
explosions in the Greek capital of Athens and the northern port of
Thessaloniki.
</P>
<P>
Two policemen were slightly hurt when a powerful explosion
rocked an Athens building, Tuesday afternoon, where a branch of
the Commercial Bank of Greece is based.
</P>
<P>
Police said the explosive device had been placed in the
mezzanine of the building.
</P>
<P>
An anonymous caller claimed the blasts were the action of a
group calling itself the "Revolutionary Core".
</P>
<P>
In Thessaloniki, the blast occurred at an olive oil plant
Tuesday morning, injuring two people and destroying a tank.
</P>
<P>
Police said the explosion took place in the plant's olive oil
storage tanks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
