<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Croatia Advance with 1-0 Victory over Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BORDEAUX, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Croatia advanced into the
quarter-finals after beating Romania 1-0 in a match far below
expectation.
</P>
<P>
The two teams played cautiously in the first half and the pace
was slow, perhaps because of the heat. The Romanians dominated the
first 10 minutes of play but soon gave the advantage to the Coratian
team.
</P>
<P>
The Croatian team had their first shot at the 10th minute and
since then they never looked back.
</P>
<P>
Aljosa Asanovic outshone Romanian playmaker Gheorghe Hagi who
looked tired in the match while Davor Suker and Zvonimir Boban posed
greater threat to the Romanian goal.
</P>
<P>
The deadlock was broken at the 44th minute when the Croatians
were awarded a penalty kick. Suker made no mistake in converting
the shot to put his team 1-0 ahead.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian team made three substitutions in the second half,
trying to get an equaliser. But their efforts were all let down by
their poor finishing.
</P>
<P>
The Croatian team had several more scoring chances in the second
half, but the shots from Boban, Asanovic and Suker were all blocked
by the brave Romanian goal-keeper Bogdan Stelea.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian team were disallowed at least two Penalty shots in
the last minutes by the Argentine referee and had to settle for the
1-0 defeat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
