<HEADLINE> Doohan Chases to Win 50th Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Michael Doohan is aiming to
capture the 50th victory of his career as Sunday's motor cycling
500cc British Grand Prix at Donington Park.
</P>
<P>
The win could put the 33-year-old Australian ahead in the world
championship points standings for the first time this season.
</P>
<P>
Doohan goes into the eighth round of the world championship
trailing Italy's Max Biaggi by three points with the Spanish duo
of Alex Criville and Carlos Checa also in contention.
</P>
<P>
Doohan, has a strong pedigree at the 2.5-mile circuit in the
English midlands, winning the last three races there. But he
dislikes the circuit, complaining of a lack of grip. 
</P>
