<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Aims to Keep HIV Infections Below 1.5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- China will try to keep the number
of HIV infections below 1.5 million by 2010, said vice health
minister Yin Dakui here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"Provided that HIV prevalence among the adult population in
China can be kept below 0.2 percent, the best achievable target by
2010 is to keep the number of HIV infections below 1.5 million,"
Yin told the 12th World AIDS Conference being held in Geneva.
</P>
<P>
The medium and long term plan for the prevention and control of
AIDS (1998-2010) has been formulated by the departments under the
State Council. Its objective up to the year 2010 is to keep the
prevalence of HIV infection in the Chinese adult population at a
relatively low level for the global context.
</P>
<P>
As for the medium objectives for HIV prevention and control by
2002, those outlined in the plan include halting the transmission
of HIV through blood collection and supply; controlling the rapid
spread of HIV in intravenous drug users; and bringing down the
increasing annual rate of sexually transmitted diseases (STD)
incidence to under 15 percent.
</P>
<P>
The goal of AIDS prevention and control is to establish a
comprehensive prevention and control system and to disseminate
information about HIV/AIDS prevention among the Chinese
population, Yin said.
</P>
<P>
To achieve the above-mentioned goal, he said, China will
intensify publicity and education on HIV/AIDS by using all forms
of press media.
</P>
<P>
Yin said that knowledge of AIDS prevention and control should
be integrated into the curriculum in high schools and
universities. Condom promotion should be encouraged according to
the situation.
</P>
<P>
The law on AIDS infection control should be established and the
formulation of regulations and rules should be sped up, Yin said.
</P>
<P>
From the identification of the first case of HIV infection in
China in 1985 to the end of March 1998, a cumulative total of more
than 10 million people underwent testing for HIV antibodies, 9,970
cases of HIV infection were reported in individuals in 30
provinces, autonomous regions or municipalities, according to Yin.
</P>
<P>
He said that there had been 290 cases of AIDS, and 173 deaths
in China. HIV infections in ethnic minorities account for 36.3
percent of the total cumulative reported infections for the
country.
</P>
<P>
Intravenous drug users account for 66.9 percent of all those
infected with HIV, Yin said. The proportion attributable to sexual
transmission is rising annually.  
</P>
</TEXT>
