<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chirac Favors Full Partnership Ties With Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June, 30 (Xinhua) -- The visiting French President
Jacques Chirac said here Tuesday that France wishes to establish
"all-round economic partnership ties" with Angola.
</P>
<P>
At a special parliamentary meeting held in his honor, Chirac
said that the French government would like to offer aid for the
development of Angola, adding that he also wishes Angola to
become a "all-round economic partner", in which the private
sectors are a dynamic in investment and promoting the diversity
of trade.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said that his government would continue to aid Angola
in its economic and social development. During Chirac's current
visit, the two sides decided to strengthen cooperation in
education, health, culture, and rural development.
</P>
<P>
At a joint press conference with his Angolan counterpart
Eduardo dos Santos, the French president said that it is
necessary to reach certain agreement with the International
Monetary Fund (IMF) when a country is faced with a crisis or
difficulty, though the agreement might be conditioned.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said that he would try to persuade IMF to take a
flexible attitude toward Angola.
</P>
<P>
On Angola's 800 million French Franc debt, Chirac called for
the joint effort by the the international community to write off
Angola's debt.
</P>
<P>
He said that he is on Angola's side in this issue.
</P>
<P>
France and Angola signed a guiding agreement for the two
countries' future cooperation, a press cooperation accord on
training Agolan journalists, a trade accord and an Agreement on
civil aviation cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The French president arrived in Luanda for a two-day visit to
Angola with an aim to boost economic ties with Angola.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
