<HEADLINE> Jiang Meets Representatives of Central Institutions in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin Thursday
called on the Central institutions stationed in the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) to work together with Hong
Kong residents to overcome the current economic difficulties and
build a better tomorrow for Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with leading members of the Central institutions
stationed in Hong Kong at the Bank of China Tower Wednesday
afternoon, Jiang, who came here Tuesday to attend the celebrations
to mark the first anniversary of Hong Kong's return to China, said
he was impressed by the warm reception of the Hong Kong people and
the profound sentiment between the people of Hong Kong and the
inland areas.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also general secretary of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China and chairman of the Central Military
Commission, said Hong Kong now faces with temporary economic
difficulties due to the impact of the Asian financial turmoil.
</P>
<P>
Jiang commented that these difficulties came beyond people's
will and were not because of China's resumption of the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
It is more important to find out the cause of the difficulties
and the ways to overcome them through joint efforts, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He also spoke of Hong Kong's advantages -- solid economic
fundamentals, abundant financial and foreign reserves, sound
economic supervision system, well educated and trained civil
servants and close links with China's inland areas.
</P>
<P>
"We can handle the challenges well as long as we have
confidence," he said.
</P>
<P>
When told that the interest rate was lowered here Wednesday,
Jiang commented that this "is good for Hong Kong".  
</P>
</TEXT>
