<HEADLINE> Indian Prisoners High-Risk Group for Infections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 1 (Xinhua) -- India's prisoners are among the
high-risk groups for sexually-transmitted diseases and blood-borne
infections, said a latest study available here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Nearly a quarter of the inmates surveyed were found to be
homosexuals, according to a study by scientists at the All India
Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS).
</P>
<P>
The pilot study among 240 male and nine female prisoners at the
Ghaziabad jail also revealed a high prevalence of
sexually-transmitted diseases and blood-borne diseases like
hepatitis and HIV among the inmates. What is aiding the diseases'
spread is sexual promiscuity and drug abuse. 
</P>
</TEXT>
