<HEADLINE> Two Goods Train Derailments Reported in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Two goods trains derailed in
India within 24 hours, hitting normal traffic on Delhi-Saharanpur
section of Uttar Pradesh in North India, official sources said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Four wagons of a goods train derailed between Sujra and Alawal
stations in Uttar Pradesh's Baghpat district Tuesday, affecting
traffic on the Delhi-Saharanpur section of northern railways.
</P>
<P>
This was the second derailment between the two stations within
24 hours and it occurred just four hours after traffic was
restored following Monday's derailment of 25 wagons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
