<HEADLINE> Religious Groups Donate to Flood Victims in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Religious groups in Fujian province
today donated more than 440,000 yuan for those who have suffered
from severe floods in this east China province.
</P>
<P>
Torrential rains soaked most parts of the province on June 12-23,
causing heavy floods in the Minjiang River area. Twenty-one
counties and 590,000 people were affected, including 126 deaths
and 50 missing.
</P>
<P>
Total losses reached 8.28 billion yuan, including 5 billion
yuan in the farming sector as 658,000 hectares of farmland was
destroyed. 
</P>
