<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Meets Hong Kong SAR Principal Officials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
Wednesday urged the civil servants of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) to continue to work for Hong Kong's
prosperity and stability.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa and
principal officials of the Hong Kong SAR and noted figures here
Wednesday afternoon, Jiang thanked them for their arduous work
over the past year on behalf of the Central Government.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also general secretary of the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China and chairman of the Central
Military Commission, said that earlier in the day he witnessed the
happy life of elderly people at Sha Tin Hospital and was very much
impressed with the warm response from Hong Kong people in Sunshine
City, a shopping center at Ma On Shan.
</P>
<P>
He said that under Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa's leadership,
the SAR officials and people in different quarters had worked
diligently and made great efforts to implement the principles of
"one country, two systems", "Hong Kong people administering Hong
Kong" and a high degree of autonomy, maintain Hong Kong's
prosperity and stability, and fend off the effects of the Asian
financial turmoil.
</P>
<P>
He said Hong Kong met with difficulties due to the impact of
the financial turbulence, but difficulties also meant challenges.
In face of difficulties, the Hong Kong civil servants and the more
than six million Hong Kong compatriots should unite more closely
and make concerted efforts to meet the challenges.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his conviction that Hong Kong's various government
departments will perform their duties under the leadership of the
Chief Executive and, at the same time, rely on the general public
and pool the wisdom and efforts of everyone so as to overcome the
difficulties and do everything well for Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Jiang came to Hong Kong Tuesday afternoon to attend
celebrations marking the first anniversary of Hong Kong's return
to China and the establishment of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Qian Qichen was present at the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
