<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Loses 20.09 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the Bombay
Stock Exchange (BSE) market Wednesday lost 20.09 points to
3,230.60 as against Tuesday's close of 3,250.69.
</P>
<P>
The national index also dropped by 11.04 points to 1,416.19 as
against the previous close of 1427.23.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar index were quoted down at 322.23
and 126.86 compared with the previous close of 325.84 and 127.74
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The BSE sensitive index fell by over 20 points Wednesday in the
wake of renewed pressure from operators as foreign funds and
financial institutions kept aloof following news of the air strike
launched by the United States against the reported Iraqi missile
strike.
</P>
<P>
Dealers also attributed the downtrend to the prevailing
unstable political situation in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
