<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kiriyenko Urges Duma's Support for Economic Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Sergei
Kiriyenko appealed to the State Duma (lower house) on Wednesday
for support for an austerity package by the government to halt the
decline of the economy.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko said Russia must carry out a stabilization program to
cooperate with the International Monetary Fund in resolving the
economic problems of the country.
</P>
<P>
The package includes measures to cut the country's spending by
about 42 billion rubles (6.77 billion U.S. dollars), and increase
revenues by about 20 billion rubles (3.23 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
Russia's gross domestic product lost 0.2 percent during the
first five months of this year, a contrast against the 0.8 percent
growth registered last year.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko highlighted reform of taxation as the basis for
boosting Russia's economy. He said a new tax code should be
adopted and "the tax burden should be shifted from the production
to the consumption sector".
</P>
<P>
It is necessary to reduce the profit tax and lift the turnover
tax, he said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the problem of repayments to the coal industry,
Kiriyenko said the wage debts are being cleared and the government
is meeting the timetables of debt repayment to the
industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
