<DOCNO> XIE19980701.0083 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE>   Tokyo Banquet Marks H.K. Handover Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 1 (Xinhua) -- An affiliate of China's Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) gave a grand banquet here
Wednesday evening to mark the first anniversary of Hong Kong's
return to China.
</P>
<P>
More than 600 guests, including Japanese government officials,
business leaders and representatives from all walks of life in
Japan attended the banquet hosted by the Economic and Trade Office
of the SAR in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
Paul Leung, Chief Representative of the trade office, said in a
speech that transition in the SAR was smooth and seamless after
Hong Kong's return to its motherland last July.
</P>
<P>
"Apart from the obvious visible changes, such as the new flags
and the new symbols, the majority of the people (in Hong Kong)
would not have noticed any change at all" over the past year. This
was because the "one country, two systems" concept was fully
implemented, Leung said.
</P>
<P>
"The principal officials who were in place before the handover
are still there running Hong Kong under a high degree of
autonomy," he said.
</P>
<P>
Talking about the recent economic downturn following the Asian
financial turmoil, Leung expressed his belief that the SAR would
surely overcome the short-term difficulties to scale even greater
heights as the new century approaches.
</P>
<P>
Guests were shown a video describing major events in the SAR
over the past year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
