<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Index Goes Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Karachi Stock Exchange
(KSE)-100 Index Wednesday closed 16.45 points down at 863.17
points as against Tuesday's close of 879.62.
</P>
<P>
A total of 114.05 million shares were traded Wednesday as
against Tuesday's turnover of 123.91 million.
</P>
<P>
There were 31 gainers and 37 losers. 
</P>
