<HEADLINE> Greenpeace Activists Stage Demonstration in Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 1 (Xinhua) --The Greenpeace activists staged
Wednesday a demonstration outside the Greek Environmental
Ministry, demanding that immediate measures be taken to deal with
the smog problem in the capital which is now experiencing a
heatwave.
</P>
<P>
Chanting the slogan "take measures before they take our
measurements," the Greenpeace activists set up a coffin outside
the ministry to draw attention to the deadly combination of
atmospheric pollution and rising temperatures in Athens, which are
expected to reach 42 degrees centigrade at the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The Greenpeace proposed that taxis be banned from using diesel
as fuel and funds be located to reintroduce trams in Athens and
to improve other urban transport means.
</P>
<P>
It also urged to establish incentives to promote
fuel-conserving vehicles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
