<HEADLINE> Philippines Declares All-Out War Against Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph Estrada
Wednesday declared an all-out war against organized crime
syndicates, warning drug lords that they will be hunted to
extinction during his administration.
</P>
<P>
Estrada, who is also the secretary of the Interior and Local
Governments, kicked off a nationwide campaign against organized
crimes, especially those drug-related ones, in San Juan city,
Metro Manila.
</P>
<P>
An all-out war against criminality was one of the new
president's campaign commitments. He reaffirmed this promise in
his inaugural address at the Quirino Grandstand, Manila, Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Estrada also appealed to the parents to give their "utmost
cooperation" in the fight against drugs and other forms of crimes.
 
