<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Russia has a positive attitude
towards the outcome of the talks between United States President
Bill Clinton and Chinese leaders, Russian Foreign Ministry
spokesman Vladimir Rakhmanin said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Russia welcomes the development of U.S.-Chinese relations,"
Rakhmanin was quoted by the Interfax news agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
Russia believed the normalization of relations between China
and the United States was an important contribution to the
stability and security in the Pacific region, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The development of close cooperation between Beijing and
Washington, as well as the relations between Moscow and Beijing,
would play stabilizing roles in the future and in the prosperity
of this important region of the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
Russia's goal was to develop constructive, equal and trusting
partnerships with China and the United States, he added.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin and Chinese President Jiang
Zemin are scheduled to meet in Moscow this fall to discuss further
development of their bilateral cooperation, Rakhmanin said.
</P>
<P>
President Clinton is now in China on a nine-day state
visit. 
