<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dredging Project Launched at Mouth of Yangtze River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 1 (Xinhua) -- After months of experiments, a
project to dredge the navigational channel at the mouth of the
Yangtze River began today.
</P>
<P>
The dredging project is of great importance to building the
Shanghai Port into an international shipping center, officials
said.
</P>
<P>
According to officials, the project will be carried out in
three phases. The first phase will cost 3.27 billion yuan to
increase the depth of the channel from the present 7 meters to 8.5
meters and build two dikes, 12.7 kilometers and 20 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The project has been contracted by the Shanghai Navigational
Channel Engineering Bureau and two other navigational channel
engineering bureaus from the Ministry of Communications. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
