<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Allocates $3m for Improving Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Maritime and
Transit Service has allocated 3,043,478 U.S. Dollars to improving
the maritime services at the port of Djibouti, office of the
Ethiopian government announces Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In a news release issued here, the office officials said the
funds will be used to purchase cranes for lifting heavy cargo and
for building warehouses and other port facilities.
</P>
<P>
The warehouses are needed to improve port services and help
alleviate the problem of overcrowding at the port, and the
Djibouti government has begun the process of handing over land
required for the warehouse construction.
</P>
<P>
According to an earlier announcement made by the Ethiopian
government, about 300 freight trucks are moving a total of 6,000
tons a day through Djibouti, and Ethiopian customs employees in
Djibouti and other stations are working 24 hours a day in two
shifts to cope with the
increase in traffic.
</P>
<P>
After the breakout of Ethio-Eritrea border dispute on May 6,
Ethiopia has diverted from Assab port of Eritrea to port of
Djibouti as its outlet. About 70 percent of Ethiopia's export and
import goods used to transit through port of Assab, which was one
of Ethiopia's two seaports before the independence of Eritrea in
May, 1993.
</P>
<P>
The port of Djibouti is linked with Ethiopia by both road and
rail.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980701.0100 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hubei Province to Protect 1,777-Year-Old Historical Relics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hubei Province has
launched a three-year protection project on the 1,777-year-old
capital of the Wu Kingdom during the Three Kingdoms Period
(220-280).
</P>
<P>
Located in Ezhou City, the historic town was built in 221 as
the first capital of the Wu Kingdom, which ruled the middle and
lower reaches of the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
With a total investment of 70 million yuan, the province will
rebuild palaces of the king's family, dredge the moat around the
town, and repair an ancient trade street. 
</P>
</TEXT>
