<HEADLINE> 36 Arrested in World Cup Violence: Organizers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-six people have been arrested in
clashes mainly between England and French youths after England lost to
Argentina in penalty shootout in Saint-Etienne, organizers said here
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Thirty-six people have been arrested according to information
received here before eight o'clock this morning," said a World Cup
French Organizing Committee spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said these arrests were made for different charges,
including theft, disrupting the public order, public drunkness,
violence against police, aggression and identification card problems.
</P>
<P>
He said there was no incident on the trains taking fans from
Saint-Etienne to Paris, which were escorted by special police force.
</P>
