<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The establishment of an
anti-corruption agency, an auditing body and a Customs office in
the future Macao Special Administrative Region has been put on the
agenda of the Administrative Group of the Preparatory Committee
for the Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
The suggestions were put forward at the committee's second
meeting on Monday and Tuesday in Zhuhai, a south China city next
to Macao.
</P>
<P>
Members of the group pointed out that setting up such agencies
complies with the Basic Law and Macao's realities. If the
Portuguese administration has any ideas in this respect, they
should hold consultations with the Chinese side through the
Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group, they said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting held extensive discussions on localizing civil
servants in the future Macao SAR and passed a draft resolution
urging the Portuguese government to speed up the process, which is
to be submitted for examination and approval by the second meeting
of the preparatory committee.
</P>
<P>
Also, it discussed the leadership composition of the future
Macao SAR.  
