<HEADLINE> Largest Coal Exporter Issues 'A' Shares on Shanghai Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Yanzhou Coal Mining Group
Co. Ltd., the largest Chinese coal exporter, has become the first
Chinese coal mining company to issue both A and B shares after
being listed on the Shanghai Stock Exchange today.
</P>
<P>
The Yanzhou Group issued 72 million A shares in Shanghai
today. The company listed H shares on both the Hong Kong Stock
Exchange and the New York Stock Exchange early this year.
</P>
<P>
The company now is also the largest coal producer in east
China with a designed annual production capacity of 13.75 million
tons. Last year the company produced 19 million tons of coal and
ranked first among Chinese coal companies in terms of sales
income, taxes and profits.
</P>
<P>
Zhao Jingche, president of the company, said today that the
company planned to increase its production capacity to 27 million
tons within five years through purchasing more coal mines and
improving work efficiency.  
