<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Another 65,000 Angolans Rendered Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Unstable situation in Angola has
rendered another 65,000 people refugees in last two months,
according to statistics of the United Nations Humanitarian Aid
Coordination Institution.
</P>
<P>
Francesco Strippoli, representative of the UN organization,
said the new refugees, are mostly from Bengo, Huila, Malanje,
Lunda-norte, Lunda-sul, Huambo and Uije provinces where the
situation is getting worse.
</P>
<P>
The unexpected refugee problem created more difficulties for
the UN organization, which along with some non-govermental
organizations, has offered aid to only 33,000 of the 654,000
refugees, Strippoli said.
</P>
<P>
The situation might get worse as the UN organization has an
emergency aid of only 2.1 million U.S. Dollars available, and
most donor nations found that many repatriated refugees have
turned back to the refugee status again, he said.
</P>
<P>
The UN organization, he said, has decided to hand over the job
to its branch organizations at the grass-root units and the
Angolan social welfare departments.
</P>
<P>
The mounting destructive activities by the opposition National
Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA) are said to
have forced many villagers to flee their homes, with 70,000
refugees created in the January to April period alone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
