<HEADLINE> HKSAR Celebrates Its First Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Various celebrations were held
here Wednesday to mark the first anniversary of Hong Kong's return
to China and the founding of the Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
A grand carnival was held Wednesday afternoon. Braving
scorching summer sun, thousands of Hong Kong residents flocked to
the Happy Valley, the only ground for horse racing on Hong Kong
Island and now the venue of the carnival.
</P>
<P>
Starting at 3:00 p.m. local time, the carnival featured various
stalls, where people were queuing up for games and small
souvenirs, visited an exhibition on the Basic Law, and watched the
performance by a police band.
</P>
<P>
The games were designed to help Hong Kong people have a better
understanding of the motherland, the "One Country, Two Systems"
principle and the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
A jigsaw puzzle was designed to familiarize people with the map
of China. There were also questions such as "how many
nationalities are there in China?"
</P>
<P>
Some 1,000 people were already waiting outside the venue an
hour before the beginning of the carnival.
</P>
<P>
When night falls, there will be a choir staged by teachers and
students, a show by popular singers and the performance by the
band of the People's Liberation Army's Hong Kong Garrison. The
carnival is due to end at 10:00 p.m.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, the Provisional Regional Council organized a
sports and games carnival in the "New Territories" to celebrate
the first anniversary of Hong Kong's historic return to China.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 70 leisure facilities in the region were opened to some
80,000 residents. A mass tai-chi, Chinese flag dance and
percussion music performances were staged.
</P>
<P>
A double-deck bus carrying banners with slogans reading "Warmly
celebrate the first anniversary of the establishment of the
HKSAR", "Hong Kong's future will be brighter" drove through
streets in the district of Kwun Tong, drawing the attention of
huge crowds of local residents all along.
</P>
<P>
Also in Kwun Tong, representatives from various sectors cut a
cake with a candle on it as a special way to mark the first
birthday of the HKSAR.  
</P>
</TEXT>
