<HEADLINE> Popular Science Exhibition Opens in Hangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of children expressed
their amazement at the gigantic man-made caterpillars, spiders and
other insects, which are hundreds of times bigger than the real
ones at a popular-science exhibition here.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, with the theme "human and nature," began this
morning at a science museum in Hangzhou, capital of east China's
Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Those gigantic insects were designed for such American films as
"Jurassic Park." Because they are a combination of advanced
techniques with perfect artificial models, these insects can mimic
the movements of real ones.
</P>
<P>
Also on display are rare conches from the Mediterranean Sea,
the West Pacific Ocean and the Atlantic Ocean, as well as
performing parrots.
</P>
<P>
The two-month exhibition aims to provide the youngsters with a
chance to learn more about popular science and to enjoy themselves
on their summer holiday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
