<HEADLINE> China Calls for Emergency Anti-Flood Effort </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- China's State Flood Control and
Drought Relief Headquarters has called for provincial and
municipal governments in in the Yangtze and Huaihe River valleys
to immediately implement flood control measures to ensure safety
in mainstream areas.
</P>
<P>
The lower and middle reaches of the Yangtze River have been
subject to rising water levels in recent weeks due to the heavy
volume of water in Boyang and Dongting lakes. Numerous sections of
the river have water levels either approaching or exceeding record
highs. Weather forecast calls for even more heavy rain in the
upper reaches of the Yangtze and Huaihe river valleys in coming
days.
</P>
<P>
Government departments have been urged to remain alert for
flooding and ensure coordinated flood control efforts. The
circular issued by the headquarters also calls for the
construction of extensive water conservation projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
