<HEADLINE> Hubei Province Gets Ready to Fight Major Flood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 1 (Xinhua) -- More than 100,000 people have been
mobilized in central China's Hubei Province to work
around-the-clock on the dikes and dams of the Yangtze River that
are threatened by floodwaters.
</P>
<P>
According to the State Meteorological Bureau, heavy rain will
hit most parts of the province in the next few days, with some
areas expected to have rainfall of 15-to-20 centimeters.
</P>
<P>
The anticipated rain will add risk to the main rivers and
reservoirs whose water levels have risen to near danger levels by
excessive rain along the upper reaches of the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The province has taken a series preventive measures to fight
the flood, including clearing flood-relief channels and
reinforcing dikes and dams. 
</P>
