<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Banquet Marks Handover Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
joined some 1,000 Hong Kong people at a banquet here Wednesday
evening hosted by the Government of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) marking the first anniversary of Hong
Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
At 7 p.m. (local time), Jiang and his wife Wang Yeping walked
into the banquet hall at the Hong Kong Exhibition and Convention
Center Extension in the company of SAR Chief Executive Tung Chee
Hwa and his wife Betty Tung.
</P>
<P>
Both Tung Chee Hwa and Vice Premier Qian Qichen spoke at the
function.
</P>
<P>
Tung recalled that one year ago, President Jiang solemnly
announced to the world the formal establishment of the Hong Kong
SAR at this very building.
</P>
<P>
In the past year, he said, there was a growing number of Hong
Kong people who came to realize from the bottom of their heart the
mutual dependence and important relationship between Hong Kong and
its motherland through the implementation of the concept of "one
country, two systems" and their fight against the Asian financial
turmoil.
</P>
<P>
Tung said: "Hong Kong is able to ride one storm after the other
in the turmoil because we have huge fiscal reserves, robust
monetary system, prudent financial management and most important
of all, the backup of our motherland."
</P>
<P>
"The strong support we have from our country makes us feel more
strongly the care and warmth of the big family of our motherland,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the concept of "one country, two systems", Tung said,
"we have the opportunity to meet new challenges that no one
generation in the past has ever met and the opportunity to take
part in the great and exciting mission of the revival of the
Chinese nation."
</P>
<P>
"We are now faced with financial difficulties, and the
difficulties are considerable. But I believe that with courage,
confidence and composure, Hong Kong will firmly tide over this
difficult time and will have a bright future ahead, " he said.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Qian Qichen extended festival congratulations to
the people from all walks of life in Hong Kong on behalf of
President Jiang and the Central People's Government.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that since the SAR was founded last July, more than
six million Hong Kong compatriots have successfully written the
first page for "one country, two systems", "Hong Kong people
administering Hong Kong" and a high degree of autonomy backed by
the Central People's Government and the people of all
nationalities.
</P>
<P>
This is a good beginning, he said. It testifies that the
concept of "one country, two systems" is completely workable and
the Hong Kong people are able to administer Hong Kong well.
</P>
<P>
Qian reaffirmed the Central People's Government's resolve to
implement the principle of "one country, two systems" and act
strictly in accordance with the Basic Law and go all out to
support Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa and the SAR Government and
do its utmost to safeguard Hong Kong's prosperity and stability.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the banquet were Henry Ying-tung Fok and Ann
Tse-kai, vice-chairmen of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), as well as SAR
principal officials, members of the executive and legislative
councils and well-known figures.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from foreign consulates-general in Hong Kong
were also on hand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
