<HEADLINE> Successful Year for Hong Kong SAR: Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The past year has seen a very
successful implementation of the concept of "one country, two
systems," Hong Kong newspapers said Wednesday, the first
anniversary of Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong's return to the motherland a year ago is a major
event in the history of the development of both the Chinese nation
and the world," the Chinese-language newspaper Wen Wei Po said
editorially.
</P>
<P>
"Inspired by the strengthening of the overall power of the
motherland and increase of its international fame and influence
and fully backed by the central government, the Hong Kong people,
under the effective leadership of the Special Administrative
Region (SAR) government, have successfully implemented the concept
of 'one country, two systems'," the paper said.
</P>
<P>
"The historic concept has won increasing support from the Hong
Kong people. And more and more people at home and abroad have come
to understand and accept the concept raised by late Chinese leader
Deng Xiaoping, and it has become a common treasure for the whole
mankind," the paper stressed.
</P>
<P>
The paper listed the factors behind the successful
implementation of the concept, which are the central government's
full support, the effective administration by the SAR government
led by Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa and the involvement and
participation of the Hong Kong residents.
</P>
<P>
"The success of the concept in the Hong Kong SAR is believed to
help push Macao's return next year to the motherland and more and
more compatriots in Taiwan will come to believe that the concept
is also applicable there," the newspaper added.
</P>
<P>
"A recent survey carried out in Taiwan showed more people than
ever before there have come to believe that the concept is
applicable in Taiwan. And some organizations have called upon the
local authorities to begin negotiations with the mainland on the
country's reunification in accordance with the concept," another
Chinese language paper Ta Kung Pao said in an editorial.
</P>
<P>
"Reunification is an irresistible historical trend and the only
way out for Taiwan is a peaceful reunification (with the mainland)
through implementing the concept of 'one country, two systems',"
the paper added.
</P>
<P>
"The Hong Kong SAR has in the past year withstood the impact of
the Asian financial turmoil and consolidated the foundation for
its prosperity and stability, to the satisfaction of the Hong Kong
residents, the central government and the international
community," Hong Kong Commercial Daily commented in an editorial
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"China's central government is fully confident of the Hong Kong
people, believing that they love the motherland and Hong Kong,
they are serious in implementing the concept of 'one country, two
systems' and they are capable of managing local affairs," it said.
</P>
<P>
"Through the efforts of the Hong Kong people, the local economy
will recover soon," the paper concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
