<BODY>
<HEADLINE> '98 China Dunhuang Trade Fair Fruitful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The four-day '98 China Jiuquan
Dunhuang Trade Fair ended today in the tourist city of Dunhuang,
northwest China's Gansu Province, with agreements reached on 38
projects worth 630 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The projects focus on cooperative investment, property rights
transfer, land sales, and trade, a local official said.
</P>
<P>
The local government adopted 29 preferential policies in the
effort, and presented 197 projects at the fair, involving
agriculture, commerce, transportation, and tourism.
</P>
<P>
Jiuquan Prefecture, where Dunhuang lies, has long been known
for its caves, frescoes, and statues, is rich in soil and
water resources, mineral and tourism resources, and boasts
convenient means of transportation and telecommunications.
</P>
</TEXT>
