<HEADLINE> Henan Reports Successful Grain Procurement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan Province
has been successful in procuring and storing summer grain,
official statistics indicate.
</P>
<P>
Henan, one of China's leading grain producers, had stored 1.598
billion kg of wheat by June 25, about 48 percent of the official
quota this year.
</P>
<P>
Partly due to unsmooth circulation and marketing, Henan's
storage of grain has totaled 18 billion kg this year, about 10
billion kg more than the normal years.
</P>
<P>
To ensure the successful implementation of the national grain
circulation system, Henan has taken all possible measures to
expand its grain storage capacity. The current storing capacity of
10 billion kg is largely enough to store newly procured grain.
</P>
<P>
No IOUs have been issued to farmers in exchange for their grain
harvest, a provincial government official said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the province has also revoked the licenses of some
private grain peddlers to ensure order in grain procurement.
</P>
</TEXT>
