<HEADLINE> Carnival Held in Celebration of HK's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A grand carnival was held here
Wednesday afternoon to celebrate the first anniversary of Hong
Kong's return to China and the founding of the Special
Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
Braving the scorching summer sun, thousands of Hong Kong
residents flocked to the Happy Valley, the only ground for horse
racing on Hong Kong Island and now the venue of the carnival.
</P>
<P>
The carnival started at 3:00 p.m. local time, featuring various
stalls where people were queuing up for games and small souvenirs,
an exhibition on the Basic Law, and performances by a police band.
</P>
<P>
According to Cheng Yiu-tong, spokesman for the organizer, a
joint conference for the celebration of the first anniversary, the
games were designed to help Hong Kong people have a better
understanding of the motherland, the "One Country, Two Systems"
principle and the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
A jigsaw puzzle was designed to familiarize people with the map
of China. There were also questions such as "how many
nationalities does China have."
</P>
<P>
"We want to promote civic education through relax and happy
games," Cheng told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
He was quite satisfied that the carnival received warm
response. Some 1,000 people were waiting outside the venue an hour
before the carnival began.
</P>
<P>
When night falls, there will be a choir staged by teachers and
students, a show by popular singers and the performance of the
band of the People's Liberation Army's Hong Kong Garrison. The
carnival is due to end at 10:00 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
