<HEADLINE> Anhui Province Invests Heavily in Housing Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, July 1 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province plans to
set up the housing sector as a major areas of economic growth,
with this year's budget calling for investments of 14 billion yuan
(1.7 billion US dollars) for housing development.
</P>
<P>
Anhui plans to complete the construction of 18 million square
meters of housing, up 10 percent on 1997.
</P>
<P>
The completion of new housing will raise the province's
per-capita housing space to 8.8 square meters.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Anhui invested a total of 3.5 billion yuan
(422 million US dollars) in housing development during the first
five months of the year, up 16 percent on the 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
Anhui Province commenced housing construction on over six
million sq.m. during the period, up 20 percent on the 1997 period,
with the area of construction completed growing by nine percent
to 3.5 million square meters.
</P>
<P>
Housing covering 538,000 sq.m. was sold from January to May, up
61.3 percent on the same period last year, with total sales
growing by 97.5 percent to 620 million yuan (74.7 million US
dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
