<HEADLINE> Liaoning Marine Industry Enjoys Rapid Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province expects the output value for its marine industry to grow
dramatically to over 40 billion yuan (4.8 billion US dollars) this
year.
</P>
<P>
"The booming marine industry has emerged as a new area of
growth in Liaoning's economy," according to Zhang Hongsheng,
director of the provincial marine and aquatic products industry
department.
</P>
<P>
The industry recorded a 1997 output value of 35 billion yuan
(4.2 billion US dollars), with this year's figure expected to grow
by 14 percent, a figure significantly higher than budgeted growth
for the provincial gross domestic product.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning, one of China's leading industrial centers, introduced
plans to develop its marine industry in 1986, with the sector
having since recorded average annual growth of 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
To date, off-shore Fishing still accounts for a 45 share of
the marine industry, down dramatically from 70 percent in 1985,
Zhang said, adding that the maritime travel industry currently
accounts for 20 percent of the total output value for the marine
industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
