<HEADLINE> Taiwanese Investment Up In Southwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Taiwanese companies have been
increasing their investment in southwest China's Sichuan Province
in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Taiwanese have funded approximately 900 enterprises in Sichuan,
with a total of 800 million U.S. dollars worth of investment, more
than in any other provinces and regions in the central and western
parts of the mainland.
</P>
<P>
A local official says that Taiwanese have also diversified and
improved their investment, with more money going into chemicals,
electronics, and other high-tech industries.
</P>
<P>
Some large companies from Taiwan are also investing in
Sichuan. High-tech Taiwanese-backed firms in Chengdu, the
provincial capital, had 480 million yuan (57.8 million US dollars)
in combined output value and 15 million yuan (1.8 million US
dollars) in profits.
</P>
<P>
Taiwanese businesspeople have also made investment in some
relatively remote areas which abounds with natural resources.
 
</P>
