<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Strives to Curtail Desertification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The State Natural Science Fund
Committee (SNSFC) plans to provide five million yuan for
scientific studies to curb desertification.
</P>
<P>
Desertification represents a major ecological problem which has
attracted global attention. Problems related to expanding
desertification currently affect some 2.6 million sq.km., or
27 percent of the nation's total land area.
</P>
<P>
Ecologists point out that desertification has seriously
affected many aspects of the national economy, degraded the
productivity of land, decreased crop yields and threatened the
nation's transportation, water conservation and national defence
infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The SNSFC project will place priority on research related to
the balance between water and other natural materials in the
ecological system, as well as the causes of desertification in
different climate zones and regions. The project will establish a
comprehensive system to curb desertification involving different
climates and land-use characteristics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
