Iraq was an appropriate response, Bill Richardson, U.S. ambassador
to the United Nations, said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the Pentagon said Tuesday that a U.S. F-16
aircraft fired at the Iraqi radar site after the Iraqi radar
locked on to allied aircraft patrolling a no-fly zone. Speaking to
reporters, Richardson said, "There was a violation of military
protocol. This is simply an appropriate response to a
violation. That is the American position." (UN-US-Iraq-Attack)
