<HEADLINE> US Companies Increase Investments in Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Official statistics indicate that
companies from the United States have substantially increased
their investments in east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
Some 23 multinational corporations from the United States,
including AT&AMP;T, Coca Cola and Dupont, had invested more than 2.65
billion US dollars in Shandong by the end of May. American
companies rank third in total investments following companies from
Hong Kong and the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
An official from the provincial commission for foreign economic
and trade affairs noted that American investments in Shandong,
China's third largest economic powerhouse, has continued to grow
during 1998.
</P>
<P>
U.S. investors signed some 60-odd investment contracts in the
first quarter of this year, up 23 percent on the 1997 period, and
pledged investments surged 110 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
American companies invest mainly in the telecommunications,
pharmaceutical and machine-building sectors, according to the
official.
</P>
<P>
The 2,390 U.S.-funded enterprises in Shandong had a combined
1997 sales volume of 128 billion yuan.  
</P>
