<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China City Planning Large Urban Construction Spending </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The capital of east China's Shandong
Province has plans to spend 28 billion yuan (3.37 billion US
dollars) on urban development in the next five years for more than
20 key construction projects, according to the deputy mayor, Tao
Anling.
</P>
<P>
The projects are expected to greatly change the old industrial
city's infrastructure and urban setting, Tao said. One is a
73-km ring road, with an estimated cost of five billion yuan (600
million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Other projects include expansion at the airport, water and gas
facilities, developing green areas and parks, and building several
large residential buildings.
</P>
<P>
Tao went on to say that housing construction alone will use 15
billion yuan (1.8 billion US dollars) during the five-year
period. Funds will come from state and local coffers, bank loans,
real estate development, and foreign government loans.
</P>
<P>
Far-sighted overseas investors are welcome to invest in Jinan's
urban construction, Tao says.
</P>
<P>
A number of large companies from the United States and Britain
have already invested in water and power plants.  
</P>
</TEXT>
