<HEADLINE> Danish Coach Tips Jorgensen As Star of Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Denmark's Swedish coach Bo Johansson
said Martin Jorgensen would be a star of the future for Denmark.
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old Jorgensen plays for Italian club Udinese and
holds a record of 34 caps for the Danish under-21 team.
</P>
<P>
Johansson didn't start Jorgensen in Denmark's matches in the
France'98 World Cup finals, but as a substitute, Jorgensen has proved
that he has the ability to be the new prince of Denmark football.
</P>
<P>
"It is wonderful for Danish football that there is a player like
Martin coming through just as Michael Laudrup retires," said
Johansson.
</P>
<P>
"The great thing about Martin is his versatility. Michael
Laudrup is one of the greatest footballers of his generation, but I
think Martin's all-round game is even better." Johansson said.
</P>
<P>
Johansson said:"It is certainly fair to say that we see him as
Michael's natural replacement. There are a lot of similarities
between the two of them."
</P>
<P>
Jorgensen has always played on the right wing for Denmark, but
Johansson said he was even betteron the left from where he loves to
cut inside from the wing and run at defenders.
</P>
<P>
It is not clear if Johansson would put Jorgensen in Denmark's
starting line-up for the quarter-final match against hosts France.
</P>
