<HEADLINE> Chongqing Security Bureau Prosecutes Major Drug Cases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Police in Chongqing, the newest
municipality located in southwest China, has investigated 603
major drug cases and confiscated over 70,000 grams of heroin over
the past year.
</P>
<P>
A senior police officer said that Chongqing's unique
geographical location has made it transit point for the drug trade
which has spread from southwest China's border areas to inland
China in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Statistics for the past year indicate that Chongqing's public
security departments have prosecuted some 3,015 drug cases and
arrested 11,264 drug addicts and drug dealers.
</P>
<P>
The municipality has intensified its crack down on drug
trafficking by establishing an anti-drug committee responsible for
mobilizing the general public in efforts to fight drug-related
crimes.
</P>
<P>
The municipality's public security departments have placed
priority on eliminating the emerging drug wholesale market and
criminal rings involved in the drug trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
