year following their removal as special duties ministers last
November in a major cabinet reshuffle.
</P>
<P>
The special advisers, especially Wada Nas, played a major role
in the campaign for Abacha to succeed himself as a civilian
president in October this year.
</P>
<P>
Also on Wednesday, Idris announced the sack of National
Security Adviser Alhaji Ismaila Gwarzo. He was replaced by
retired Major-General Abdullahi Mohammed, the first
director-general of the Nigerian secret police, the National
Security Organization, now the State Security Service (SSS).
