<HEADLINE> 14 Killed in Road Crash in N. Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen persons were killed Tuesday
on a highway in northern Nigeria's Jigawa State in an accident
involving a pick-up and a trailer.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses were quoted by Wednesday's Daily Times as saying
that the van was returning from a market, loaded with goods, when
the accident took place. Nobody survived.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of the deceased have been deposited in a hospital,
awaiting collection by their relatives.
</P>
<P>
Pick-up vans and similar "open" vehicles are popular means of
conveying people in the state. No fewer than 40 travellers have
died in similar circumstances on the road to neighboring Knao
State so far this year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Federal Road Safety Commission has pledged to
embark on an enlightenment campaign to educate motorists and
other road users on proper behavior on the highway. 
