<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Additional Trains Operates from Today for Summer Holidays </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- China's Railway Ministry will
operate additional trains from today through August 31, or the
regular summer holidays for college students.
</P>
<P>
Some 48 long-distance high-speed trains and 32 short-distance
passenger trains will be put into use during the period.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Ministry of Railway is expected to have to handle
169 million passengers during the 62-day period, a 2.8 percent
increase from 1997. About 46 million will be travel 500 kilometers
or more each trip, 12 percent more than for the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
To cope with train passengers' needs, especially long-distance
travelers, the Ministry will add more temporary trains on the
Beijing-Yantai, Beijing-Ganzhou, Beijing-Yanzhou, and
Yingtan-Xiamen routes and will increase the trains' handling
capacity on the Beijing-Shanghai, Beijing-Guangzhou, and
Beijing-Harbin runs.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, railway departments are also expected to add ticket
windows and to keep them open longer hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
