<DOCNO> XIE19980701.0205 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong SAR Publishes First Honors List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) government published here on Wednesday
its first full Honors List since Hong Kong's return to China last
July.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong SAR Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa has accorded an
honor or award to a total of 230 persons on the List, which was
published in the Government Gazette on Wednesday, in recognition
of their personal contribution to Hong Kong or for their devotion
to the public and community, the government said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Among the four receiving the top honor of the Grand Bauhinia
Medal was Arnaldo de Oliveira Sales, the former president of the
Amateur Sports Association and Olympic Committee of Hong Kong,
China, for his contribution to the development of amateur sports
and the Olympic movement in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Ng Hong-mun is awarded for his outstanding public and community
service and his contribution to the preparatory work for the
establishment of the SAR; Run Run Shaw is honored for his
distinguished contribution to the development of the local film
and television industries in Hong Kong and to the development of
the performing arts, education and welfare services; and Wong
Po-yan is awarded GBS for his contribution to the development of
the new Hong Kong International Airport at Chek Lap Kok and his
long and distinguished public and community service in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Two Gold Medals for Bravery were awarded to Lee Ying-kwong, a
local resident who was swept to death while trying to save two
boys in a flood in June this year, and Thomas Fredrick Crosier
Larmour, a policeman, who died while trying to rescue two young
men from the sea during a typhoon last August.
</P>
<P>
The awards are to be presented later this year, the government
statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
