<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets Belarussian Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao
said today that China will join Belarus in effort to further
the overall development of friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Hu made the remarks this morning during a meeting with visiting
Belarussian Foreign Minister Ivan Antonovich. He said China fully
respects the development path Belarus has adopted in accordance
with its own national conditions and attaches great importance to
furthering relations with the country.
</P>
<P>
Hu noted that Sino-Belarussian relations have grown steadily
since the two countries forged diplomatic ties, with constant
high-level contacts and positive results in bilateral exchanges
and cooperation in various fields.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have also enjoyed good cooperation in
international affairs, said Hu.
</P>
<P>
He also spoke highly of the achievements Belarus has recorded
in recent years and expressed hope that the country and its people
will enjoy continuing prosperity and happiness.
</P>
<P>
