<HEADLINE> Guangdong Mobilizes Flood Relief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The government of Guangdong
Province, south China, has called for local governments and the
general public to act promptly to battle flooding which has
devastated major portions of the province and continue threatening
well-being and property of local residents.
</P>
<P>
Torrential rains since the middle of June have filled
reservoirs to capacity and caused flooding along all major
rivers. Some 81 people have either died or are missing, with
direct economic losses estimated at 1.64 billion yuan (205 million
US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Provincial leaders and relevant provincial departments are
co-ordinating resue operations supported by the People's
Liberation Army units.
</P>
<P>
The local meteorological station reports that Guangdong
continues to face threats from the coming flood season. 
</P>
