Party (PKK) militants.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a war since 1984 against Turkish
government in an attempt to establish an Kurdish state in
southeastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Zaman (Time):
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish Foreign Ministry Tuesday voiced its dissatisfaction
with a U.N. Security Council resolution adopted Monday to extend
the mandate of the U.N. Peacekeeping Forces in Cyprus for another
six months.
</P>
<P>
This decision marked "another repetition of the mistake that
has been made for years," the ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Yeni Yuzyil (New Century):
</P>
<P>
-- A prosecutor with the Diyarbakir State Court has proposed
that Semdin Sakik, a key member of the PKK who was captured by
Turkish special forces in April, be sentenced to death under the
125th articles of the Turkish Penal Law.
</P>
<P>
Sakik is standing trial in the court on several criminal
charges. 
</P>
