<HEADLINE> Number Of Ibis In China Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The number of crested ibis in China
is expected to be increased by 40 in China's Shaanxi Province this
year, bringing the total number to 140.
</P>
<P>
One hundred of the rare birds, which are under top state
protection, are now being cared for at the ibis protection center,
a considerable change from the 7 that were found in the wild 17
years ago.
</P>
<P>
Ornithologists attribute the increase to improvements at the
center and to increased protection for wild ibises.
</P>
<P>
They say that 14 pairs of ibis have built nests and that those
birds kept at the center are showing a stronger tendency to
reproduce than those living in the wild. 
</P>
</TEXT>
