<HEADLINE> China Rebuilding Wind Tunnels For Aerospace Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Four wind tunnels in China that are
used for testing space vehicles have passed certification tests
after a year of trial operation.
</P>
<P>
Scientists at the China Air Dynamics Research Center in Sichuan
Province in southwest China say that they have a supersonic speed
electric arc wind tunnel, a hypersonic speed wind tunnel, a shock
wave wind tunnel, and a hypersonic speed low-density wind tunnel
on which they spent six years for feasibility studies and
rebuilding.
</P>
<P>
The rebuilding work will provide more reliable ground
simulation tests for various space vehicle tests, according to
specialists.  
</P>
