<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Henan Province Establishes Unified Insurance System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan Province
launched its new unified old-age insurance system on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The system will enable workers from all Henan enterprises to open
individual old-age insurance accounts funded with monthly payroll
deductions of 11 percent.
</P>
<P>
The use and collection of individual insurance accounts will be
subject to separate management and will be strictly controlled to
avoid misappropriations.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government is currently drafting measures to
expand the scope of old-age insurance to cover foreign-funded
enterprises, as well as self-employed individuals and private
businesses in urban areas.
</P>
<P>
Some 3.79 million workers and more than 790,000 pensioners, or
80 percent of the respective totals in Henan, had participated in
varied insurance programs by the end of last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
