<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Construct Ring Road Outside Dhaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will construct a ring road
outside its capital city Dhaka in the 1998-99 financial year
beginning Wednesday to ease traffic movement in the metropolitan,
Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina said.
</P>
<P>
The construction work would begin after the feasibility study
was finished, press reports here on Wednesday quoted Hasina as
telling the parliament on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The government had also decided to set up circular rail lines
in the city, and efforts are being made to secure foreign
assistance in this regard, she said.
</P>
<P>
Several foreign companies had expressed their willingness to
set up circular rail lines under the build-operate-and-transfer
(BOT) system, according to the prime minister.
</P>
<P>
With more than 225,000 vehicles and a population of nearly 9
million, traffic jams are a common scene inside the Dhaka city,
and the situation is made worse by over 300,000 rickshaws plying
around the city every day. 
</P>
