<HEADLINE> Computerizing Yangtze River Flood Information </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 1 (Xinhua) -- China recently started using a
computerized network for flood information of the Yangtze, the
country's longest river, connecting the central flood control
authorities and areas along the river.
</P>
<P>
The network is a major step in modernizing the availability of
flood information on the Yangtze, which is vital to improving the
country's flood control, analysts say.
</P>
<P>
It also comes into existence at an especially crucial moment,
when seasonal flooding is threatening large parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
The network connects the State Flood Control and Drought Relief
Headquarters, the Yangtze River Water Conservation Committee, and
the provinces of Sichuan, Hunan, Hubei, Shaanxi, Henan, Jiangxi,
and Jiangsu within the Yangtze valley.  
</P>
