<HEADLINE> Successful Year for Hong Kong SAR: Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The past year since Hong Kong's
reunification with the motherland has proved very successful in
implementing the concept of "one country, two systems," Hong Kong
newspapers said here on Wednesday on the first anniversary of Hong
Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong's reunification with the motherland a year ago is a
major event in the history of the development of both the Chinese
nation and the world," an editorial of the Chinese-language
newspaper Wen Wei Po said.
</P>
<P>
"Inspired by the strengthening of the overall power of the
motherland and increase of its international fame and influence
and fully backed by the central government, the Hong Kong people,
led effectively by the Special Administrative Region (SAR)
government, have successfully participated in and implemented the
concept of 'one country, two systems'."
</P>
<P>
"The historic concept has won increasing support from the Hong
Kong people. And more and more people at home and abroad have come
to understand and accept the concept raised by late Chinese leader
Deng Xiaoping and it has become a common treasure for the whole
mankind," the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
The editorial cited as the reasons for the success of the
concept the central government's full support, the effective
administration by the SAR government led by Chief Executive Tung
Chee Hwa and the involvement and participation of the Hong Kong
residents .
</P>
<P>
"The past successful year for the Hong Kong SAR in the
implementation of the concept of 'one country, two systems' is a
good beginning and it has far-reaching influence on Hong Kong's
long-term development.
</P>
<P>
"The success of the concept in the Hong Kong SAR is believed to
encourage and help push Macao's reunification next year with the
motherland and more and more compatriots in Taiwan will come to
believe that the concept is also applicable there," the newspaper
added.
</P>
<P>
"The unprecedented concept of 'one country, two systems'
created by late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping was once doubted by
many. But the Hong Kong SAR government and residents, backed by
the central government and people of the mainland, have carried
out the concept creatively to make it a reality in Hong Kong,"
said an editorial by another Chinese-language newspaper, Ta Kung
Pao.
</P>
<P>
"The success of the past year has not only consolidated Hong
Kong people's confidence in the concept of 'one country, two
systems," but also set an example.
</P>
<P>
"A recent survey carried out in Taiwan showed more people than
ever before there have come to believe that the concept is
applicable in Taiwan. And some organizations have called upon the
local authorities to begin negotiations with the mainland on the
country's reunification in accordance with the concept," the
editorial said.
</P>
<P>
"Reunification is an irresistible historical trend and the only
way out for Taiwan is a peaceful reunification (with the mainland)
through the implementation of 'one country, two systems' which has
proved to be successful in Hong Kong," the newspaper added.
</P>
<P>
"The Hong Kong SAR has in the past year withstood the impact of
the Asian financial turmoil and consolidated the foundation for
its prosperity and stability, to the satisfaction of the Hong Kong
residents, the central government and the international
community," Hong Kong Commercial Daily commented in an editorial
Wednesday. "The year since Hong Kong's reunification with the
motherland has proved to be successful."
</P>
<P>
"China's central government has a high degree of confidence in
the Hong Kong people, believing that Hong Kong residents love the
motherland and Hong Kong, they are serious in implementing the
concept of 'one country, two systems' and they are capable of
managing local affairs," it said.
</P>
<P>
"The past successful year has laid a solid foundation for the
future development of Hong Kong. Through the efforts of the Hong
Kong people, the historic concept will surely be implemented in a
better and mature way and Hong Kong's economy will recover soon to
bring a new look to the Hong Kong SAR when it enters the 21st
century." the paper concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
