<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand Overhauls Plan To Boost Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The ministry will establish three regional commercial offices
to handle some tasks now performed by the ministry's central
office, such as the trademark and corporate registration.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Trade Department's three commodity standard
divisions will be merged and two new ones will be established, one
to counter dumping of underpriced foreign goods on the Thai market
and the other to deal with subsidies.
</P>
<P>
The Commercial Registration Department will be dissolved, with
the task of oil quality inspection moving to the National Energy
Policy Office.
</P>
<P>
Senior officials will also discuss ways of updating 42 laws
affecting the ministry's operations.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's exports have shrunk by almost 3 percent in the
second quarter of this year despite the devaluation of the baht.
</P>
