<HEADLINE> Sino-US Power Station Planned For Northwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and United States investors
will back a power station in the city of Dunhuang, the site of the
world-famous Dunhuang Grottoes, in north China's Gansu Province.
</P>
<P>
According to an agreement signed last weekend, four Chinese
companies and the Tang Energy Group, Ltd. of the United States
will put 278 million yuan (33.5 million U.S. dollars) on a
50,000-kilowatt gas turbine power station in Dunhuang.
</P>
<P>
