<HEADLINE> China Donates 27 Jeeps to Cambodia for Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government Wednesday
donated 27 Beijing jeeps worth 250,000 U.S. dollars to Cambodia's
National Election Committee (NEC) Wednesday for the general
elections scheduled for July 26.
</P>
<P>
The hand-over ceremony was held at the Interior
Ministry. Present at the ceremony were Chinese Ambassador Yan
Tingai to the Kingdom of Cambodia and Cambodia's Secretary of
State for Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation Uch Kim
An, the NEC chairman and Vice-chairman.
</P>
<P>
Kassie Neou, the NEC vice chairman, said,"the Kingdom of
Cambodia are especially grateful to the Chinese authorities for
their timely help. It will contribute greatly to the success of
the upcoming elections."
</P>
<P>
He also thanked China for other assistance to the Cambodian
people, which serves to improve agricultural productivity and the
livelihood of the residents of the rural areas.
</P>
<P>
"In my view, the NEC is slowly but surely succeeding in its
difficult task of making Cambodia's elections free, fair,
transparent and peaceful," added Kassie Neou.
</P>
<P>
Yan Tingai said the upcoming election is a major event in
political life of the Cambodian people.
</P>
<P>
He hopes that the elections will be held on schedule and go
smoothly and peacefully and that Cambodia will enter a stage of
long-term stability and peaceful period after the elections.
</P>
<P>
Yan also assured the Cambodian government that Chinese
observers would actively take part in the free and fair
observation process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
