<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Interview: Brunei Strives to Diversify Economy (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Metali said that for the primary resources sector, the Brunei
government has a keen interest in maintaining an efficient and
export-oriented agricultural sector with the strategy focusing on
the production of selected priority products such as poultry,
tropical fruits and vegetables and that of orchid and other
high-value ornaments.
</P>
<P>
Venturing into downstream activities like food processing,
repackaging and redistribution of agricultural produce has also
been encouraged, he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that in the fisheries sector, there are three areas --
capture fishing, aquaculture and fish processing -- which are
extremely promising revenue earners.
</P>
<P>
For forestry development, he said, more than 80 percent of
Brunei's land area is covered by forest, giving rise to forestry
as one of the major economic activities in the country.
</P>
<P>
Considering the environmental and social needs, he pointed out,
the government has acted to conserve some 320 square kilometers or
about 5.5 percent of the country's land area as forest reserves
and allocated 500 square kilometers for a national park and a
further 20 square kilometers of the forest-covered land to be
turned into recreational facilities. In addition, 3 percent of the
country's total land area has been designed as protection forests.
But still 38 percent or 2,200 square kilometers of the country's
land area has been set aside as production forests, he said.
</P>
<P>
In manufacturing which is a high-priority development sector
under the IDP, identified to receive immediate attention are food
and beverage, silica and clay products, textiles and apparel,
electrical appliances, electronics and hi-tech industry, building
materials, processing and repackaging activities, metal and
non-metal products, furniture, biotechnology-based industry, and
downstream oil and gas manufacturing activities.
</P>
<P>
For services development, he said, Brunei is actively promoting
and encouraging high value-added activities such as tourism,
consultancies, construction, maintenance, air and sea linkages,
telecommunications, insurance and re-insurance.
</P>
</TEXT>
