<HEADLINE> China's Prosperity Ripples Through Neighbors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BISHKEK, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Kyrgyzstan is set for a boom period
in the next century as long as it maintains its cooperation with
China, Kyrgyzstan President Askar Akayev said.
</P>
<P>
China's prosperity would lead to development and progress in
Kyrgyzstan, said Akayev shortly before attending a meeting of five
leaders from Kyrgyzstan, Kazakhstan, Tadzhikistan, Russia and
China, in Alma-Ata on July 3 and 4.
</P>
<P>
He told Chinese correspondents that China had a vital role in
promoting regional peace, stability and security.
</P>
<P>
"I am very happy to have established personal ties with Chinese
President Jiang Zemin. We keep regular contacts and understand
each other," said Akayev.
</P>
<P>
"It is very precious for statesmen. Without mutual trust, it is
difficult to resolve some interstate issues. I think mutual trust
and friendly relations lay a good foundation for expanding
friendship between peoples and economic and trade cooperation."
</P>
<P>
Kyrgyzstan appreciated the implementation by Chinese leaders of
a policy of good neighborliness, he said .
</P>
<P>
Akayev praised Chinese President Jiang for fully demonstrating
his wisdom with regard to border issues.
</P>
<P>
He mentioned that, at Jiang's suggestion, China, Russia,
Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan had signed an agreement in
Shanghai on April 26, 1996, on establishing military confidence in
border areas.
</P>
<P>
"This was a historic event, making the longest border in the
world a peaceful and cooperative border, thus setting a good
example for the international community," said Akayev.
</P>
<P>
During Jiang's visit to Kyrgyzstan two years ago, the two
countries signed historical agreements, removing all political
obstacles to better relations.
</P>
<P>
Economic and trade cooperation showed great potential, said
Akayev adding that China was Kyrgyzstan's third biggest trading
partner.
</P>
<P>
He thanked China for opening road and air services to
Kyrgyzstan. China and Kyrgyzstan started direct air service
between Bishkek and Beijing on May 16, cutting the flight, which
previously went via Moscow, by half.
</P>
<P>
The building of the Osh-Kashi road link was in full swing and
the second border port between the two countries would be put into
operation in autumn next year, according to Akayev.
</P>
<P>
On the Taiwan issue, Akayev restated there was only one China,
the People's Republic of China, and Taiwan was an inalienable part
of the Chinese territory.
</P>
<P>
He said Kyrgyzstan and Chinese leaders shared the same stance
in opposing separatism. "We backed China's opposition of
separatism in the past and we continue doing so." 
</P>
</TEXT>
