<HEADLINE> U.S. President Clinton Visits Shanghai Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Visiting U.S. President Bill
Clinton this noon visited the Shanghai Stock Exchange, the first
of its kind in China.
</P>
<P>
The exchange was established in December of 1990 and has
A-shares, B-shares, funds, treasury bonds, enterprise bonds and
financial bonds, among others.
</P>
<P>
At the end of May this year, 407 enterprises were listed on the
stock exchange, and there are 446 kinds of stocks with their
combined market capitalization reaching 1.1867 trillion yuan
(about 143 billion U.S. dollars).  
</P>
