<HEADLINE> Jiang: Hong Kong will Overcome Economic Difficulties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said here today that he was confident that Hong Kong would be able
to overcome the current economic difficulties resulted from the
Asian financial turmoil.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a ceremony marking the first anniversary of Hong
Kong's return to China at the Hong Kong Coliseum, Jiang said: "The
current difficulties will be overcome and there are conditions and
capabilities of doing so. We have full confidence in this."
</P>
<P>
He listed a string of Hong Kong advantages -- a solid economic
foundation with ample fiscal and foreign exchange reserves, a
sound regime of financial regulation and supervision, and a
contingent of high-caliber civil servants and sophisticated
businessmen with rich experience in management and in adapting to
international market changes.
</P>
<P>
Although the impact of the Asian financial turmoil has not gone
away and Hong Kong's economic difficulties will continue for some
time, he said, "Hong Kong is still one of the universally
recognized most competitive regions."
</P>
<P>
Jiang called on the Hong Kong compatriots to build up their
sense of responsibility as masters of the country and their
confidence in overcoming difficulties. The great motherland would
be a strong backing for Hong Kong, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We are convinced that Hong Kong will bring its advantages into
full play, overcome the temporary difficulties and achieve even
greater development," the Chinese leader said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
