<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Grand Ceremony Marks SAR First Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A grand celebration meeting
marking the first anniversary of Hong Kong's return to China and
the establishment of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR) was held at Hong Kong Coliseum here Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin attended the meeting and
delivered an address.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also General Secretary of the Central Committee
of the Chinese Communist Party and Chairman of the Central
Military commission, said that the development in the year since
Hong Kong's return to the motherland has fully demonstrated that
adherence to the policies of "one country, two systems", "Hong
Kong people administering Hong Kong" and a high degree of autonomy
and strict compliance with the Basic Law of the HKSAR constitute
the fundamental guarantee for long-term prosperity and stability
in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"Practice will continue to prove that the policy of 'one
country, two systems' will help to not only safeguard the
interests of people of different social strata in Hong Kong, but
also maintain Hong Kong's status as the international financial,
trading and shipping center," Jiang pointed out.
</P>
<P>
"We note with pleasure that the HKSAR Government headed by Mr.
Tung Chee Hwa has administered Hong Kong capably and effectively
over the past year in vigorously resolving issues relating to the
welfare and well-being of Hong Kong residents that are of
universal concern in Hong Kong, handling its internal and external
affairs steadily and surely and taking up challenges calmly, in
particular, in fending off the impact of the Asian financial
turmoil," the Chinese president said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang told the meeting, which was attended by thousands of
people from all walks of life in Hong Kong, that the situation in
China's inland areas is "good". "Despite the Asian financial turmoil,
we enjoy social and political stability and sustained economic
growth," Jiang added.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR), said at the meeting that the "one
country, two systems " concept worked out remarkably well in the
past year. Most important of all, the successful implementation of
the "one country, two systems" concept manifests that the people
of Hong Kong have truly become masters of their own destiny.
</P>
<P>
Their addresses were followed by a song and dance performance
by artists from both Hong Kong and the inland areas.
</P>
<P>
Among those present at the celebration gathering were Chinese
Vice Premier Qian Qichen, Member of the Secretariat of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China Zeng Qinghong, Chief of
the General Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA) Fu
Quanyou and Director of the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office
under the State Council Liao Hui.
</P>
<P>
Also present were HKSAR Administrative Secretary Anson Chan,
Financial Secretary Donald Tsang, Secretary of Justice Elsie
Leung, Convenor of the Executive Council Chung Sze-yuen and
president of the former Provisional Legislative Council Rita Fan.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
