<HEADLINE> Clinton Stresses Importance of Trade Links With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The success of China's economy
will have profound impact on the prosperity and stability of the
United States and the world as a whole, visiting U.S. President
Bill Clinton said here today.
</P>
<P>
In his speech at a breakfast with local and American business
persons this morning, Clinton fully emphasized the importance of
trade links with China for the U.S. economy.
</P>
<P>
"I'll do everything I can to promote and encourage the
expansion of trade relations between the United States and China,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
President Clinton said that as one of the largest trade
partners of the United States, China has brought about a large
amount of job and growth opportunities for the U.S..
</P>
<P>
He said that it is in the interests of the U.S. that the U.S.
Congress should support the granting of permanent Most Favored
Nation trade status to China.
</P>
<P>
He said that he will do everything he can to promote trade
between the two countries and to encourage American companies to
expand these relations.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that development of trade relations will help
push forward diplomatic relations between the two countries, which
in turn will facilitate the expansion of trade links.
</P>
<P>
He said that China's development is not only important for the
country's prosperity and stability, but also has profound
influence on prosperity and stability of the United States and the
world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
More than 500 people from the Chinese and American industrial
and business circles attended the breakfast held by the American
Chamber of Commerce in Shanghai for Clinton at the Portman
Ritz-Carlton Hotel where he stays.
</P>
<P>
After the breakfast, Clinton will visit the Shanghai Stock
Exchange and a local family in the Jinhui Gardens, a housing
development project in Hongqiao District in the city. 
</P>
