<HEADLINE> Jiang: Motherland Gives Strong Backing for Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said here today that the Central Government would be a strong
backing for the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) in
its effort to overcome the current economic difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Addressing at a ceremony held at the Hong Kong Coliseum to mark
the first anniversary of Hong Kong's return to China, Jiang told
Hong Kong compatriots: "The Central Government will continue to
vigorously support the SAR Government in its measures to maintain
financial and economic stability."
</P>
<P>
When the regional financial storm hit Hong Kong last year, the
Central Government went all out to back the HKSAR Government in
its counter-measures, particularly in its effort to maintain the
linked exchange rate system and the overall stability in Hong
Kong, said Jiang who is also General Secretary of the Central
Committee of the Chinese Communist Party and Chairman of the
Central Military Commission.
</P>
<P>
Jiang stressed: "This was a forceful demonstration that the
great motherland is the strong backing for Hong Kong."
</P>
<P>
"The economic strength and sound development momentum of the
mainland can provide Hong Kong's economy with a strong support,"
the Chinese leader said, adding that despite the Asian financial
turmoil, China still enjoys "social and political stability and
sustained economic growth."
</P>
<P>
He reaffirmed China's commitment not to devaluing its currency
and expressed confidence in realizing the economic development
objectives set for 1998.
</P>
<P>
Jiang stressed that the Central Government would go on to
support the Hong Kong business community in making investment in
the mainland and Hong Kong in its efforts to develop tourist
industry, high and new technology industries, infrastructure,
entrepot trade, economic and technical exchange and cooperation
with the rest of the international community.  
</P>
