<HEADLINE> Quigley Wins Tuesday's Fourth Race in Skiff Yachting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Australian Stephen Quigley Tuesday
won the fourth race of the 18-foot skiff world championship in
Fowey, England by less than a minute after a four-hour battle.
</P>
<P>
Quigley and his crew sailing Richard Ellis constantly swapped
the lead with Australians Peter Sorensen and his crew in Allegro
when the two boats went in front at the halfway stage.
</P>
<P>
Sailing in idyllic conditions off the Cornish coast, the
Richard Ellis team snatched the lead for the last time meters from
the finishing line.
</P>
<P>
The first five finished within three minutes, with British
boats Burgs third and Ovington fourth.
</P>
<P>
After Tuesday's competition, Allegro topped the championship
standings and Richard Ellis finished second followed by Burgs,
Australia's Travel Power, Oveington and Montane of Britain.
</P>
</TEXT>
