<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's EPDP Leader Stabbed by Rebel Prisoners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Eelam People's
Democratic Party (EPDP) leader Douglas Devananda Tuesday night was
stabbed with an iron implement allegedly by prisoners who are
Tamil rebel suspects at Kalutara Prison, said reports reaching
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The attack on the EPDP leader took place at around 7:30 p.m.
Tuesday when he visited the 54 prisoners who had staged a hunger
strike demanding that they be tried at courts or else be released
from the prison in Western Province, 45 kilometers from here.
</P>
<P>
Devananda was admitted to the Intensive Care Unit of the Nagoda
 and later transferred to the Colombo National Hospital.
</P>
<P>
The reports quoted hospital sources as confirming that his
condition was critical.
</P>
<P>
Police are reportedly conducting investigations into the
assault.
</P>
<P>
The EPDP, a Tamil political party, supports the Sri Lankan
government against the Tamil rebels who are fighting for a
separate state in the north and east of the country. 
</P>
