<HEADLINE> Ancient Chinese Site Being Used For Film-shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese county of Pingyao, in
north China's Shanxi Province, which has been in existence since
221 BC, has become a film location attracting Chinese film-makers
because of its ancient architecture.
</P>
<P>
It provides more realism, for films, they say, and have made a
dozen films there in the past several years.
</P>
<P>
Pingyao is well-known for its well-preserved ancient walls,
3,797 ancient houses, stores, temples, streets, and a county
government office.
</P>
<P>
It is also the birthplace of modern commerce and banking in
China, and was listed as one of the world cultural heritage sites
by UNESCO in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
