<HEADLINE> Jiang: "One Country, Two Systems" Safeguards Hong Kong Interests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said here today that practice will continue to prove that the
policy of "one country, two systems" will help not only
safeguard the interests of people of different social strata in
Hong Kong, but also maintain Hong Kong's status as the
international financial, trading and shipping center.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who arrived here Tuesday from Beijing for the occasion,
made the remarks at a ceremony marking the first anniversary of
Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
The developments since Hong Kong's return to China a year ago
have fully demonstrated that adherence to the policies of "one
country, two systems," "Hong Kong people administering Hong Kong"
and a high degree of autonomy and strict compliance with the Basic
Law of the HKSAR constitute the fundamental guarantee for
long-term prosperity and stability in Hong Kong, said Jiang, who
is also the General Secretary of the Central Committee of the
Chinese Communist Party and Chairman of the Central Military
Commission.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who declared the resuming by the Chinese government of
the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong and the establishment
of the HKSAR on July 1, 1997, said the handover was "a major event
that is forever worth commemorating in the history of the
development of the Chinese nation."
</P>
<P>
He said that as long as the policy of "one country, two
systems" is consistently followed, Hong Kong will be able to
create a better future with the support of the mainland.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also pointed out that the successful implementation of
the policy of "one country, two systems" will serve as an example
for Macao's smooth return to the motherland and for the final
settlement of the Taiwan issue.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
