<HEADLINE> hke - Hungary's Economy Grows in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Hungarian economy appeared
slightly healthier in the first quarter with its gross national
product (GNP) rising by 4.9 percent over the same period last
year, the Central Bureau of Statistics (CBS) said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
During the three-month period, Hungarian industry grew by 12
percent, construction by 17.2 percent, transportation and post and
telecommunications 6.3 percent, with agriculture and fishery down
7.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, domestic consumption and investment grew by
1.5 percent and 12.1 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the same period of 1996, the GNP in the first
three months of 1997 grew only 2.1 percent, according to CBS'
statistics.
</P>
<P>
The Hungarian GNP in 1997 increased 4.4 percent and analysts
here expected a rise of more than five percent this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
