<HEADLINE> 3.4 Kilograms of Heroin Seized in Jakarta, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian customs officers and
police detectives have arrested a Myanmar man at the Jakarta
airport for allegedly smuggling 3.4 kilograms of high-grade heroin
into the country, the local press reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 34-year-old man was handcuffed upon arrival at the
Soekarno-Hatta International Airport Monday night from Bangkok on
Thai Airways, the report quoted National Police Detective Corps
commander Brig. Gen. Da's Bachtiar as saying.
</P>
<P>
The drug, which has an estimated street value here of 4 billion
rupiah (about 276,000 U.S. dollars) was wrapped in plastic bags
and allegedly strapped under the man's bag.
</P>
<P>
During police questioning, the man reportedly admitted that he
was hired as a courier to smuggle the drug to Jakarta. He was to
hand it over to the owner, a Nigerian staying here, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a prosecutor asked Central Jakarta District Court
Monday to sentence a 35-year-old Myanmar man to death for
smuggling 4.4 kilograms of heroin into Indonesia from Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
The man was arrested on November 14 last year at Tanah Abang
Indah Hotel in Central Jakarta, the report said. 
