up by 5.08 and 0.46 percent respectively in the same period.
</P>
<P>
To promote exports, the Ecuadoran government has held a series
of negotiations with the European Union (EU) to extend the
preferential tariff generalized system for another four years.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador also negotiated with the EU on the enforcement of the
World Trade Organization's free banana transactions in the
European market and on signing trade and economic agreements,
which will help Ecuador overcome economic difficulties. 
