mortar fire from supporters of MNLF Commander Yusup Jikiri, who
ran for Sulu governor but lost to Tan, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
It said five people were killed and more than 40 others were
wounded during the attack.
</P>
<P>
The MNLF signed a peace accord with the government two years
ago to end a 30-year-old civil war in the Southern Philippines.
But some of its members have not been integrated into the
government army and the national police. 
