<HEADLINE> Brazil Registers Trade Surplus in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Brazil registered a foreign
trade surplus of 105 million U.S. dollars in June, official
figures showed.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics of the Ministry of Industry, Trade and
Tourism, exports summed up 4.450 billion dollars, while imports
went up to 4.345 billion dollars in June, the first positive
result achieved in the last 25 months.
</P>
<P>
Brazil had a trade deficit of 1.942 billion dollars in the
first quarter of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Since President Fernando Henrique Cardoso came to office in
1995, Brazil's foreign trade had witnessed an increasing deficit,
which grew from 3.15 billion dollars to 5.5 billions dollars in
1996 and peaked at 8.5 billion dollars last year. 
