<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Launch Tourism Promotion Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's tourism industry will
launch a promotion campaign dubbed "Let's Go Indonesia" that will
include allowing every foreign tourist in the country to stay one
day free of the usual charges, an industry spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The program will be carried out in July to fit in with the
vacation period in foreign countries, chairman of an Indonesian
tourism operators' association, Sri Mulyono Herlambang, said here
Tuesday, Antara News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Foreigners visiting Indonesia will be given a day when they can
enjoy free hotel accommodation, meals and transportation to places
of tourist interest.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian Tourism Promotion Board (BPPI) said recently
that the country might lose around 30,000 foreign tourists during
the June-August period this year due to recent social unrest.
</P>
<P>
For this very reason, Sri Mulyono said, the government should
revive tourism activities.
</P>
<P>
Sri Mulyono said that only 20 percent of the country's
approximately 4,200 travel bureaus are currently still operating
amidst the protracted economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
"Some of the still existing travel agencies do not sell tourism
packages anymore but tickets," he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
