<HEADLINE> HK Flag Raising Ceremony Marks SAR Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A flag raising ceremony was held
here Wednesday morning marking the first anniversary of the
establishment of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR)
of China.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa and his wife Betty Tung attended
the ceremony, which was held at the seafront promenade outside the
Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center Extension.
</P>
<P>
Henry Fok Ying-tung, vice chairman of the National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC),
Jiang Enzhu, director of Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch, and
Andrew Li Kwok-nang, chief justice of the Court of Final Appeal of
the HKSAR, were present.
</P>
<P>
Among some 500 participants of the ceremony were senior SAR
government officials, officials of the Commissioner's Office of
the Chinese Foreign Ministry in Hong Kong, officers of the
People's Liberation Army garrison in the SAR and noted local
figures.
</P>
<P>
After the national flag of the People's Republic of China and
the flag of the HKSAR were hoisted at 8:00 a.m. by Hong Kong
police officers amidst the playing of the national anthem of the
PRC, a helicopter carrying the flags flew overhead.
</P>
<P>
The flag raising ceremony attracted thousands of residents.
Some of them came before dawn get better positions to see the flag
raising.
</P>
<P>
Holding a miniature version of the Chinese national flag and
the HKSAR flag in his hands, a retired worker said he felt a
strong sense of pride when he saw the flags hoisted into the air.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong SAR was established on July 1, 1997 when China
resumed the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
