<HEADLINE> U.S. Becomes Third Largest Investor In Shandong Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The United States has become the
third largest investor in east China's Shandong Province, after
Hong Kong and the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this May, U.S. firms have invested 2.65 billion
U.S. dollars in the coastal province. Many U.S.-funded firms are
involved in manufacturing telecommunications equipment,
health-care goods and machinery products.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, U.S.-funded firms in the province, which numbered
2,390, had total sales of more than 128 billion yuan. 
