<HEADLINE> Petroleum, Gas Output of Qaidam Basin Hits Record-high </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Because of new extracting
techniques, the daily oil output of the Qinghai Oil Field, China's
fourth largest natural gas field, has increased to 5,000 tons from
the 4,500 tons produced at the end of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Located in the Qaidam Basin on the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, the
oil field has already produced more than 15.5 million tons of
crude oil and refined eight million tons of oil since 1954.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the oil field's oil and natural gas
output had hit one million tons for seven consecutive years.
</P>
<P>
The field's oil resources are estimated at 4.2 billion tons and
its verified natural gas reserve tops 150 billion cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
The annual outputs of oil and natural gas are expected to reach
three million tons by the end of this century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
