<HEADLINE> State Offers Training for Redundant Officials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Leaving current posts and waiting
for "reassignment" are part of an ongoing streamlining of
ministries and commissions under the State Council.
</P>
<P>
Today's China Daily said that officials to be reassigned could
receive professional training in eight universities, including
Beijing University and People's University of China.
</P>
<P>
These universities will open such courses as accounting, master
of business administration, auditing, finance, taxation and
foreign languages.
</P>
<P>
If recruited, they can finish their academic careers with
government aid, according to a spokesman of the Ministry of
Education.
</P>
<P>
After graduation, they will acquire academic certificates from
the nine universities in Beijing which have been authorized to
confer degrees to these special students.
</P>
<P>
Ministry and commission streamlining, proposed by Premier Zhu
Rongji at the Ninth National People's Congress in March, aims to
improve governmental efficiency by cutting redundant employees.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
