<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sea Route Links Chinese, Vietnamese Tourist Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIHAI, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The first sea route linking China
and Vietnam opened last week.
</P>
<P>
The 157-nautical-mile route links Beihai, a beach-side Chinese
city in south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, with Ha
Long in Vietnam. The trip takes about 12 hours.
</P>
<P>
The link, the first cross-border sea route ever offered in
China, is designed to take Chinese tourists (including those from
Hong Kong, but excluding those from Macao and Taiwan) to the
cities of Ha Long and Hai Phong in Vietnam, and the Vietnamese
tourists to Beihai and Qinzhou in Guangxi.
</P>
<P>
Tourist experts say the route will contribute to tourism
exchanges between China and southeast Asia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
