<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Philippine newspapers Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- With a firm voice and his left hand placed atop a
red-covered Bible, Joseph Ejercito Estrada on Tuesday swore to
serve the country and people as he took his oath as the
Philippines' 13th president inside the historic Barasoain Church
in Malolos city.
</P>
<P>
Manila Standard:
</P>
<P>
-- The international community welcomed on Tuesday the start of
the administration of President Estrada with congratulatory
messages that reaffirmed their support to the new leader.
</P>
<P>
Today:
</P>
<P>
-- Hours after taking his oath as the 13th president of the
Philippines, Joseph Ejercito Estrada on Tuesday declared his term
as the "Time of the Common People" and vowed to give the poor
their due, even as the country struggles with an economic crisis.
</P>
</TEXT>
