<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Investment Increasing in Suzhou New Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Suzhou New Area in Jiangsu
Province now has 101 Hong Kong-funded companies, with a total
investment exceeding 7 billion Hong Kong dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong-funded firms account for 32 percent of the
overseas-funded companies in the district, while their capital
makes up 24 percent of the total overseas investment there.
</P>
<P>
Since the new district was established six years ago, local
authorities have paid more attention to attracting investment from
Hong Kong. The district has opened an office there to build ties
with different industries.
</P>
<P>
As investment from other parts of the world has been on the
rise, Hong Kong investors have turned to public facilities
including gas- and water-supply projects.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures, the new district has used more
than 3.8 billion U.S. dollars from abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
