<HEADLINE> Sampras, Hingis Reach Wimbledon Quarter-Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Defending Champion Pete Sampras of
the United States enjoyed a smooth journey to the quarter-final of
the Wimbledon tennis championships early Monday after beating
Sebastien Grosjean of France in straight sets 6-3, 6-4, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
The American world number one gave his opponent no chance of
launcing counter attacks and came one step closer to defend his
Wimbledon title.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 9th seed Richard Krajicek of Netherlands and 14th
seed Goran Ivannisevic also reserved their positions in the
quarter-final knockouts after beating their separate opponents.
</P>
<P>
In the women' fourth round competitions, defending champion
Martina Hingis of Switzerland continued her unstoppable dominance
of the center court after trouncing Tamarine Tanasugarn of
Thailand 6-3, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
The other top women's seeds including third seed Jana Novotna
of Czech Republic, French Open champion Arantxa Sanchez Vicario of
Spain and 7th seed Venus Williams of the United States also
followed Hingis's steps into the next round. 
</P>
