<DOCNO> XIE19980701.0339 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Monet Painting Set Price Record Since 1990 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Claude Monet's painting "Waterlily
Pond and Path by Water" was sold for 19,801,500 pounds (33 million
U.S. dollars) in London Tuesday, becoming the most expensive
painting sold in Europe since 1990.
</P>
<P>
Auctioneers Sotheby's said it was also the highest price paid
for a work by Monet. The previous highest price for his painting
was 13 million pounds (21 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Monet, who died in 1926 at the age of 86, was a leading
impressionist artist in France.
</P>
<P>
The painting of the water garden at Monet's home at Giverny was
bought by an anonymous telephone bidder.
</P>
<P>
Monet painted "Waterlily Pond and Path by Water" in 1900, when
he spent the entire summer painting his waterlilies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
