<HEADLINE> World Bank Okays 720 Mln Dlr Loans for Mexico's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved here
Tuesday two loans totaling 720 million U.S. dollars equivalent for
Mexico.
</P>
<P>
The first loan of 700 million dollars is provided for the
country's health system reform -- the Special Basic Health Program
for the Uninsured (IMSS) project.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be utilized to support the ongoing implementation
of the government's health system reform, focusing on the
modernization of the IMSS project.
</P>
<P>
The program is designed to improve the financial management of
the health insurance system to ensure financial transparency,
introduce new resource allocation and financial mechanisms to
improve efficiency and limit the fiscal impact of the proposed
reform and strengthen the institutional and regulatory framework
for health insurance.
</P>
<P>
The other loan of 20 million dollars is offered for Mexico's
health system reform technical assistance project. This project
will support the design and implementation of major policy changes
in the health sector in the country, mainly through reforms in the
Mexico Social Security Institute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
