<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Keeper Roa Becomes Hero as Argentina Beat England </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAINT-ETIENNE, France, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Keeper Carlos Roa became
the hero for Argentina as the South Americans beat 10-man England 4-3
in the penalty shootout after two sides tied 2-2 after the extra time
in a World Cup second-round game here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Argentina reached the last eight and will face the Netherlands in
the quarterfinals in Marseille on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Roa made the decisive diving save against England's fifth shoter
David Batty after the sides were deadlocked 3-3 even from the spot.
</P>
<P>
An earlier shot from Argentina's Hernan Crespo was saved by keeper
David Seaman but England's Paul Ince also did not convert his.
</P>
<P>
Gabriel Batistuta put Argentina ahead only five minutes into this
grippling and heatly-contested game by converting a penalty kick.
</P>
<P>
Seaman dived in the right direction, touched the ball but the blast
was so powerful that the ball slipped off his hands into the net.
</P>
<P>
Referee Milton Nielsen of Denmark awarded the penalty after Seaman
brought down midfielder Diego Simeone in the area.
</P>
<P>
England equalized four minutes later also on a penalty kick, which
was kicked by Alan Shearer after Nielsen judged that defender Roberto
Ayala made a foul against striker Michael Owen.
</P>
<P>
Liverpool striker Owen found the net in the 16th minute, shotting
the ball home off the far post after beating two Argentine defenders.
</P>
<P>
But Argentine forced a 2-2 tie in the injury time through Javier
Zanetti who scored with his left foot in small angle after a free
kick.
</P>
<P>
The English attacks even did not dwindle much at first after
midfielder David Beckham was sent off only one minute into the second
half.
</P>
<P>
Shearer almost netted in the 52nd minute but his booming free kick
was lifted over the crossbar by keeper Carlos Roa.
</P>
<P>
England's Sol Campbell netted in the 81st minute but the goal was
disallowed.
</P>
<P>
Ayala squandered two Argentine chances twice in the first 15
minutes of the extra time by heading the ball twice over the bar but
the 10-man England successfully hold out to the penalty shootout.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
