<HEADLINE> World Bank Backs 3rd Social Protection Project in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Tuesday approved
a loan of 284 million U.S. dollars equivalent for Argentina's
third social protection project.
</P>
<P>
This project will finance small projects to provide temporary
financial assistance to poor workers and improve social and
economic infrastructure in poor communities.
</P>
<P>
The project acts as a social safety-net program that
complements Argentina's efforts to stimulate higher employment
through continued high growth, labor market reform, and
improvement to the quality and relevance of education.
</P>
<P>
This project is expected to finance over 15,000 projects and
employ 300,000 workers for the rehabilitation, expansion, and new
construction of potable water, sewage, housing, roads, urban
works, irrigation schools, and health centers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
