<HEADLINE> World Bank Okays 250 Mln Dlr Credit for Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved Tuesday
an interest-free credit of some 250 million U.S. dollars
equivalent for the Bangladesh health and population program
project.
</P>
<P>
This project will improve coverage and quality of essential
health and family planning services for vulnerable groups,
particularly poor women and children and support public sector
reorganization and reform efforts to achieve more cost-effective
service delivery, elimination of duplication, improved quality and
better utilization.
</P>
<P>
The project will also lay the groundwork for broader health
reform in the country.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be provided by the International Development
Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessional lending wing for
developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
