<HEADLINE> World Bank Supports Environmental Sector in Azerbajian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Tuesday approved
an interest-free credit equivalent to 20 million U.S. dollars to
support an urgent environmental investment project in Azerbajian.
</P>
<P>
The project is designed to restore the country's sturgeon
production, support environmental decontamination, and strengthen
the environmental management system.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is some 24.51 million dollars
equivalent, including contingencies. The credit will be channeled
through the International Development Association (IDA), the World
Bank's concessional lending affiliate for developing countries.
</P>
<P>
Since Azerbajian joined the World Bank in 1992, and the IDA in
1995, the country has received some 290 million dollars equivalent
for eight projects. 
</P>
